a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = (x - 1) * (x - 3) * (x - 7) * (x - 9)"
shows  "f 6 - f 4 = 0"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Define \[f(x) = (x-1)(x-3)(x-7)(x-9).\]Evaluate $f(6) - f(4)$. The final Answer is 0
 ### Proof
 We see that \[f(4) = (4-1)(4-3)(4-7)(4-9) = (3)(1)(-3)(-5)\]\[f(6) = (6-1)(6-3)(6-7)(6-9) = (5)(3)(-1)(-3).\]But then $f(4) = f(6)$, so $f(6) - f(4) = \boxed{0}$.
 *)
